38
00:03:29,290 --> 00:03:31,250
 The call is not going through. You'll be connected to the voicemail- 

39
00:03:31,250 --> 00:03:32,880
Gosh, this is nuts.

40
00:03:32,880 --> 00:03:34,860
Lee Ji Han.

41
00:03:34,860 --> 00:03:36,680
Lee Ji Han.

42
00:03:36,680 --> 00:03:38,730
Gosh! Get yourself together, seriously.

43
00:03:38,730 --> 00:03:41,580
Na A Jeong, stand straight, please.

44
00:03:41,580 --> 00:03:43,260
Are you drunk?

45
00:03:43,260 --> 00:03:46,480
You can lean on me. I'll take you home.

46
00:03:48,630 --> 00:03:51,700
I should've known. I wondered why he drank the alcohol in my place.

47
00:03:51,700 --> 00:03:53,700
If you were going to give me such a hard time,

48
00:03:53,700 --> 00:03:56,670
why did you offer me your hand there? Your hand.

49
00:03:56,670 --> 00:03:59,130
You were happy to grab it back then.

50
00:03:59,130 --> 00:04:02,600
You got mad at me when I was getting dissed earlier.

51
00:04:03,420 --> 00:04:09,430
Lee Ji Han, my house is 20 minutes on foot and five minutes by bicycle from here.

52
00:04:09,430 --> 00:04:12,790
I could've already been home, washed up, and lying down by now.

53
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:16,110
Must I be reflecting on my morals here because of you?

54
00:04:17,830 --> 00:04:21,160
This isn't the Pacific Ocean. They're my shoulders!

55
00:04:21,160 --> 00:04:23,650
You're surprised because they're too broad, right?

56
00:04:23,650 --> 00:04:26,530
That's why you're trying not to lean on me, right? I can just tell!

57
00:04:26,530 --> 00:04:28,420
- Seriously. 
 - Why?

58
00:04:28,420 --> 00:04:30,300
You don't like my shoulders?

59
00:04:30,300 --> 00:04:32,200
In that case...

60
00:04:34,900 --> 00:04:36,530
You said it takes 20 minutes on foot and

61
00:04:36,530 --> 00:04:38,220
five minutes on a bicycle. Right?

62
00:04:38,220 --> 00:04:41,520
I'll get you there in three minutes, then!

63
00:04:41,520 --> 00:04:42,910
Hey!

64
00:04:42,910 --> 00:04:44,690
Let go!

65
00:04:45,440 --> 00:04:47,520
Let go! Let go!

66
00:04:47,520 --> 00:04:49,340
Let go!

67
00:05:05,510 --> 00:05:07,390
Lee Ji Han.

68
00:05:07,390 --> 00:05:10,460
Lee Ji Han, wake up!

69
00:05:10,460 --> 00:05:12,590
Lee Ji Han.

70
00:05:19,660 --> 00:05:22,540
 The customer can't answer the call right now. 

71
00:05:23,310 --> 00:05:26,060
The boat's leaving in 10 minutes. Let's hurry.

72
00:05:26,060 --> 00:05:30,760
Hyung, it looks like I'll have to go back to Seoul.

73
00:05:34,320 --> 00:05:37,830
My Ji Han has never declined my calls for more than an hour.

74
00:05:37,830 --> 00:05:41,940
He even calls me day and night on my days off, bothering me.

75
00:05:41,940 --> 00:05:44,690
But look! He's been unreachable for 12 hours now.

76
00:05:44,690 --> 00:05:46,150
D-Does this make sense?

77
00:05:46,150 --> 00:05:49,330
Taek, this is an illness.

78
00:05:49,330 --> 00:05:52,180
It's the weekend, so he must be sleeping in or something!

79
00:05:52,180 --> 00:05:53,990
Sleeping in?

80
00:05:54,740 --> 00:05:58,940
Oh, no! He must be dead or have been kidnapped!

81
00:06:13,900 --> 00:06:17,680
 All the alcohol is gone. She can leave now, right? 

82
00:06:17,680 --> 00:06:22,670
 I think I like you enough to get pissed off if someone insulted you. 

83
00:06:22,670 --> 00:06:24,650
 You, Na A Jeong. 

84
00:06:32,120 --> 00:06:34,380
Like you, my foot.

85
00:06:35,250 --> 00:06:36,730
Feet.

86
00:06:37,700 --> 00:06:40,070
Why did you go to that woman?

87
00:06:40,880 --> 00:06:42,200
Hand.

88
00:06:42,200 --> 00:06:44,440
Why did you offer it to her?

89
00:06:45,350 --> 00:06:47,410
Brain.

90
00:06:47,410 --> 00:06:50,520
Why do you keep caring about that woman?

91
00:06:51,960 --> 00:06:53,670
Carrot?

92
00:06:55,250 --> 00:06:57,930
You're the uncle who bought my mat, right?

93
00:06:57,930 --> 00:07:00,740
- Who are you? 
 - I'm Jo Ji Ho.

94
00:07:05,500 --> 00:07:08,370
This one is one of my favorites.

95
00:07:08,370 --> 00:07:11,420
But I'll sell it to you for 5,000 won.

96
00:07:11,420 --> 00:07:14,150
- Where are we? 
 - This is Aunt's room.

97
00:07:14,150 --> 00:07:16,390
Right. So why am I in your aunt's room?

98
00:07:16,390 --> 00:07:19,830
My aunt carried you on her back last night.

99
00:07:19,830 --> 00:07:22,800
My aunt's really strong.

100
00:07:23,980 --> 00:07:25,910
What's with this dingy shirt?

101
00:07:25,910 --> 00:07:28,320
No way, did I vomit?

102
00:07:28,320 --> 00:07:29,320
Did I?

103
00:07:29,320 --> 00:07:33,110
Mom made you honey water, and you spat it back out,

104
00:07:33,110 --> 00:07:35,350
saying you hate sweet stuff.

105
00:07:38,750 --> 00:07:40,760
Okay.

106
00:07:40,760 --> 00:07:42,810
I'll buy that from you.

107
00:07:42,810 --> 00:07:44,640
Really?

108
00:07:44,640 --> 00:07:47,460
Instead, see if your aunt is outside.

109
00:07:47,460 --> 00:07:49,850
If you help me go without your aunt knowing,

110
00:07:52,780 --> 00:07:54,950
all this money will be yours, Ji Ho.

111
00:07:54,950 --> 00:07:56,580
Okay.

112
00:08:03,110 --> 00:08:04,510
Aunt's not outside right now.

113
00:08:04,510 --> 00:08:06,270
Okay.

114
00:08:10,940 --> 00:08:12,650
I was right, wasn't I?

115
00:08:12,650 --> 00:08:14,800
Aunt's not here, right?

116
00:08:17,690 --> 00:08:20,220
But she's the only one who's not here.

117
00:08:24,400 --> 00:08:27,230
Goodness gracious, all right.

118
00:08:27,230 --> 00:08:29,230
You're awake.

119
00:08:29,230 --> 00:08:31,750
Wash up and have breakfast.

120
00:08:44,860 --> 00:08:47,770
I rushed to prepare them,

121
00:08:47,770 --> 00:08:50,710
but I'm not sure if you'll like them, In-law.

122
00:08:50,710 --> 00:08:54,350
Thank you for the meal, but I'm not your in-law.

123
00:08:54,350 --> 00:08:57,740
- What? 
 - My brother and your daughter didn't marry yet.

124
00:08:57,740 --> 00:08:59,390
Oh, right.

125
00:08:59,390 --> 00:09:05,150
And who's the one who got wasted and was carried into the in-laws-to-be's house?

126
00:09:10,090 --> 00:09:12,240
Gosh, it's salty.

127
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:14,240
- Hey, look— 
 - By the way,

128
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:17,660
we all have to go out to take care of business, so help yourself and leave.

129
00:09:17,660 --> 00:09:20,010
- Did we have something to do? 
 - Y-Yes, you know...

130
00:09:20,010 --> 00:09:22,240
- Oh, really? 
 - Honey? Ji Ho.

131
00:09:22,240 --> 00:09:23,640
- Come here. 
 - Wait, why?

132
00:09:23,640 --> 00:09:27,290
- Huh? 
 - Let's talk outside.

133
00:09:31,960 --> 00:09:34,250
 We had nothing to do. 

134
00:09:34,250 --> 00:09:37,460
One word from you and look at us.

135
00:09:37,460 --> 00:09:39,840
Why do we have to get kicked out of our house?

136
00:09:39,840 --> 00:09:42,580
I just didn't know what to say.

137
00:09:42,580 --> 00:09:45,580
Anyhow, Honey, is my cooking salty these days?

138
00:09:45,580 --> 00:09:49,640
Gosh, I should've put less salt in the soup.

139
00:09:49,640 --> 00:09:53,030
Gosh, forget it. He would've said it's bland, then.

140
00:09:53,030 --> 00:09:56,420
That jerk just doesn't like us, not the soup.

141
00:09:56,420 --> 00:09:58,270
I like that uncle, though.

142
00:09:58,270 --> 00:10:01,920
You know, he showed up dressed in money from head to toe last time

143
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:04,960
and dragged Sis to go with him without any explanation.

144
00:10:04,960 --> 00:10:10,460
But the point is the infamous Na A Jeong didn't say a word and got in his car.

145
00:10:10,460 --> 00:10:12,750
- A Jeong did? 
 - She didn't say a word?

146
00:10:12,750 --> 00:10:14,260
Yes!

147
00:10:14,260 --> 00:10:20,220
I think Sis is feeling really down right now because she's marrying a conglomerate.

148
00:10:20,220 --> 00:10:23,640
Don't you think her brother-in-law-to-be will actually be the biggest problem?

149
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:28,380
He's already giving Sis a hard time even before she enters the wedding hall, thinking he has the right.

150
00:10:28,380 --> 00:10:29,820
Right?

151
00:10:29,820 --> 00:10:33,280
I mean, he looked clean-cut.

152
00:10:33,280 --> 00:10:36,360
I guess his personality's completely different from his brother's.

153
00:10:36,360 --> 00:10:37,750
Mother.

154
00:10:37,750 --> 00:10:42,780
They say to look at a person's eyes to see their nature, not the face, right?

155
00:10:42,780 --> 00:10:46,360
But that in-law's eyes just glare the wrong way.

156
00:10:46,360 --> 00:10:50,760
 His eyes are already humongous, and they're too glaring, on top of that. 

157
00:10:50,760 --> 00:10:54,040
The swallow was grateful and brought gourd seeds. 
  (Referring to Korean folktale) 

158
00:10:54,040 --> 00:10:57,150
The magpie was grateful and sacrificed its life.

159
00:10:57,150 --> 00:10:59,950
But why is Lee Ji Han, a human being, the only one who is ungrateful and turning on me?

160
00:10:59,950 --> 00:11:02,950
Speaking of, what kind of nonsense is this, Na A Jeong?

161
00:11:02,950 --> 00:11:06,450
This is clearly kidnapping.

162
00:11:06,450 --> 00:11:08,500
As soon as I woke up, the scammer kid and the flowery blanket.

163
00:11:08,500 --> 00:11:10,870
Do you know how flustered I was?

164
00:11:10,870 --> 00:11:15,510
I was going to call the police, but the warm meal changed my mind. Just so you know.

165
00:11:18,650 --> 00:11:20,950
You don't remember what happened last night?

166
00:11:24,390 --> 00:11:25,720
You don't.

167
00:11:25,720 --> 00:11:30,770
You said your shoulders were as broad as the pacific ocean, but I guess your memory's as narrow as a stream.

168
00:11:30,770 --> 00:11:33,190
What about last night?

169
00:11:33,190 --> 00:11:35,640
I brought you out of the hotel,

170
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:37,900
I apologized, and it's the end. Isn't it?

171
00:11:37,900 --> 00:11:41,350
I thought you'd be like this. So I recorded it all.

172
00:11:43,490 --> 00:11:47,710
Here's the first evidence to prevent you from feigning ignorance.

173
00:11:47,710 --> 00:11:49,440
 Come out now. 

174
00:11:49,440 --> 00:11:52,380
 Come out. Are you sleeping, huh? 

175
00:11:57,860 --> 00:11:59,130
 Please enter it again. 

176
00:11:59,130 --> 00:12:03,370
 Gosh! Hey, are you looking down on me? 

177
00:12:03,370 --> 00:12:05,650
 Open up while I'm being nice. 

178
00:12:16,820 --> 00:12:19,420
 Hey, we're at a club! 

179
00:12:20,460 --> 00:12:23,350
 Beep, bop, beep, bop. 

180
00:12:26,110 --> 00:12:28,260
 Ji Ho, record me, please. 

181
00:12:28,260 --> 00:12:30,040
 Carrot? 

182
00:12:30,040 --> 00:12:31,620
 - Mom! 
 - Wait... 

183
00:12:31,620 --> 00:12:33,150
 Gosh, help me, please. 

184
00:12:33,150 --> 00:12:34,860
 G-Gosh, why are you all gathered here? 

185
00:12:34,860 --> 00:12:38,010
 - Honey. 
 - O-Open the door! 

186
00:12:40,600 --> 00:12:42,540
 I don't want it. I hate sweet stuff! 

187
00:12:42,540 --> 00:12:45,820
 Gosh, we need to change his clothes. I'm sure this is an expensive shirt. 

188
00:12:45,820 --> 00:12:47,760
 - Mom. 
 - Hey, hey, hey. 

189
00:12:47,760 --> 00:12:49,830
 Stop recording and wipe him. 

190
00:12:49,830 --> 00:12:51,830
 He's your brother-in-law, not mine! 

191
00:12:51,830 --> 00:12:55,670
 - This is uncomfortable. I'm taking it off! 
 - Gosh- 

192
00:12:56,500 --> 00:12:58,490
 He's nuts! 

193
00:13:00,470 --> 00:13:03,520
Well, did your sense of conscience return?

194
00:13:03,520 --> 00:13:05,360
What's that?

195
00:13:06,940 --> 00:13:08,750
Give it.

196
00:13:08,750 --> 00:13:10,990
I said hand it over!

197
00:13:10,990 --> 00:13:13,040
What would you have done without me?

198
00:13:13,040 --> 00:13:15,650
You'd have passed out on the hotel floor.

199
00:13:15,650 --> 00:13:19,000
It would've been cold and embarrassing, and you would've been totally humiliated.

200
00:13:19,000 --> 00:13:21,250
And who'd hear it? Your grandfather.

201
00:13:21,250 --> 00:13:24,520
It's better to die on the streets than to be humiliated like this.

202
00:13:24,520 --> 00:13:26,510
You blackmailer.

203
00:13:27,560 --> 00:13:31,710
Blackmailing is your specialty. What I'm doing right now is negotiating.

204
00:13:34,210 --> 00:13:36,700
I'll erase it for you.

205
00:13:36,700 --> 00:13:38,310
But acknowledge it.

206
00:13:38,310 --> 00:13:39,400
Acknowledge what?

207
00:13:39,400 --> 00:13:44,050
That I will never fall for you, nor anyone else.

208
00:13:44,050 --> 00:13:46,980
I was dragged to Busan and to a blind date.

209
00:13:46,980 --> 00:13:50,520
I've cooperated with you more than enough, Lee Ji Han.

210
00:13:50,520 --> 00:13:53,970
- It's your turn now. 
 - And what if I say no?

211
00:13:53,970 --> 00:13:57,410
It can't be helped, then. I already have lots of evidence,

212
00:13:57,410 --> 00:14:02,090
so I'll have to tattle on you for everything that happened to Do Han.

213
00:14:03,010 --> 00:14:05,020
Tattle?

214
00:14:05,020 --> 00:14:06,950
I don't think you can.

215
00:14:06,950 --> 00:14:09,550
Because I'll get rid of all your evidence.

216
00:14:40,100 --> 00:14:42,550
You said you started to like me...

217
00:14:43,350 --> 00:14:46,890
enough to get pissed off if someone insulted me.

218
00:14:46,890 --> 00:14:51,310
Since you like me now, can't you also just acknowledge Do Han and me?

219
00:14:53,260 --> 00:14:57,050
Then, I think I might like you a little bit, too.

220
00:15:12,140 --> 00:15:18,360
   

221
00:15:28,830 --> 00:15:30,980
- Let me see your phone. 
 - What?

222
00:15:30,980 --> 00:15:32,720
Why?

223
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:44,150
Your phone's fine, and you're fine as well.

224
00:15:44,150 --> 00:15:46,780
So, what on Earth happened yesterday?

225
00:15:46,780 --> 00:15:48,950
You know, right?

226
00:15:48,950 --> 00:15:52,140
I always have an excuse for everything.

227
00:15:52,140 --> 00:15:55,690
But I've got nothing to say to excuse myself today.

228
00:15:55,690 --> 00:15:57,690
Go on.

229
00:15:57,690 --> 00:15:58,780
I'll take the scolding.

230
00:15:58,780 --> 00:16:01,750
I couldn't reach you at all until the district office hours ended.

231
00:16:01,750 --> 00:16:04,220
But why'd you suddenly leave tens of missed calls,

232
00:16:04,220 --> 00:16:06,710
only to not answer when I called you back?

233
00:16:06,710 --> 00:16:09,250
- I'm sorry. 
 - I couldn't reach you and

234
00:16:09,250 --> 00:16:11,450
the studio was in shambles.

235
00:16:11,450 --> 00:16:13,150
Do you know how worried I was?

236
00:16:13,150 --> 00:16:16,850
But what about the studio?

237
00:16:16,850 --> 00:16:18,570
Did something happen?

238
00:16:18,570 --> 00:16:22,910
This isn't the right place to talk about it, so let's go inside.

239
00:16:22,910 --> 00:16:26,550
You can talk here! Just talk here.

240
00:16:28,310 --> 00:16:30,730
He can call her if he has something to tell her.

241
00:16:30,730 --> 00:16:33,540
Why the heck did he come in person this early in the morning?

242
00:16:38,600 --> 00:16:40,290
- A Jeong. 
 - Yes?

243
00:16:40,290 --> 00:16:42,560
I'm not asking you to marry me as a joke.

244
00:16:42,560 --> 00:16:43,770
I know.

245
00:16:43,770 --> 00:16:47,880
If I can't reach you like yesterday, that's a breach of contract—

246
00:16:47,880 --> 00:16:51,680
 What's she doing? Why is she covering Brother's mouth? 

247
00:16:51,680 --> 00:16:53,490
I know.

248
00:16:53,490 --> 00:16:56,600
That's enough. I'll make sure it doesn't happen again.

249
00:16:56,600 --> 00:16:58,010
So, nothing happened, right?

250
00:16:58,010 --> 00:16:59,480
Yes.

251
00:16:59,480 --> 00:17:01,540
I'm glad, then.

252
00:17:03,210 --> 00:17:05,040
I think someone's going in and out of the studio.

253
00:17:05,040 --> 00:17:08,350
- What? 
 - The plane ticket was all ripped apart.

254
00:17:08,350 --> 00:17:10,140
We'll have to be careful for a while.

255
00:17:10,140 --> 00:17:12,930
Hey, d-did you call the police?

256
00:17:12,930 --> 00:17:16,350
- I don't want to complicate things. 
 - Hey, you still need to call the police about this!

257
00:17:16,350 --> 00:17:17,900
What's your deal, seriously!

