00:48:12,380 --> 00:48:15,810
I invited her. She's my guest.

755
00:48:20,420 --> 00:48:23,380
What are you all doing? Aren't you going inside?

756
00:48:27,780 --> 00:48:33,500
   

757
00:48:42,120 --> 00:48:44,830
   

758
00:48:51,290 --> 00:48:55,110
A Jeong, one moment.

759
00:48:59,710 --> 00:49:02,090
Say hello.

760
00:49:02,090 --> 00:49:04,910
She'll be your daughter-in-law.

761
00:49:04,910 --> 00:49:07,710
I allowed her in your place because she

762
00:49:07,710 --> 00:49:10,450
seems to like Do Han a lot.

763
00:49:13,280 --> 00:49:15,400
Let her greet you now.

764
00:49:16,080 --> 00:49:17,830
Go ahead.

765
00:49:26,080 --> 00:49:28,680
It looks like a reporter had visited.

766
00:49:28,680 --> 00:49:34,190
He was curious about the truth of the only daughter of a conglomeratefamily who suddenly disappeared without a trace.

767
00:49:35,200 --> 00:49:39,290
Mr. Ji Han probably knew nothing

768
00:49:39,290 --> 00:49:42,650
 about what kind of a person his mother used to be. 

769
00:49:57,500 --> 00:49:59,260
 Hello, kid. 

770
00:49:59,260 --> 00:50:00,670
 Who are you? 

771
00:50:00,670 --> 00:50:03,070
 Your mother's name is Hyeon Soo Hyeon, right? 

772
00:50:03,070 --> 00:50:04,450
 Do you know my mom? 

773
00:50:04,450 --> 00:50:08,510
 Of course. I'm your mom's friend. 

774
00:50:08,510 --> 00:50:12,300
 It's pouring. Let's go home. 

775
00:50:12,300 --> 00:50:15,260
What would an eight-year-old kid even know?

776
00:50:15,260 --> 00:50:17,180
He said he was his mother's friend

777
00:50:17,180 --> 00:50:19,860
and that he'll take him home.

778
00:50:19,860 --> 00:50:22,830
He was excited and said yes.

779
00:50:22,830 --> 00:50:25,330
It rained a lot that day.

780
00:50:25,330 --> 00:50:29,610
He was trying to lose the reporter and ended up in an accident.

781
00:50:35,920 --> 00:50:40,260
 - Soo Hyeon! Soo Hyeon!  
 - Chairman said he still doesn't understand

782
00:50:40,260 --> 00:50:42,510
why he had decided to do that.

783
00:50:42,510 --> 00:50:45,400
 Soo Hyeon! Soo Hyeon! 

784
00:50:45,400 --> 00:50:48,270
 - Soo Hyeon...  
 - One thing that's for sure is

785
00:50:48,270 --> 00:50:52,880
he still regrets that decision to this day.

786
00:50:56,900 --> 00:51:02,710
I'm sure it was the same for Grandfather but it was too cruel of an accident for Lee Ji Han.

787
00:51:03,590 --> 00:51:09,860
That's why Mr. Ji Han still hates rainy days the most.

788
00:51:10,800 --> 00:51:14,290
I guess he's reminded of that day.

789
00:51:36,730 --> 00:51:40,830
Why's she looking at me with such wet eyes? It'll make fungi grow on me.

790
00:51:41,720 --> 00:51:43,450
- Grandfather. 
 - Yes.

791
00:51:43,450 --> 00:51:45,510
- Did you hear the news? 
 - What?

792
00:51:45,510 --> 00:51:51,070
CEO Yoon is helping out with resuming the Myeongju shopping mall complex project.

793
00:51:51,070 --> 00:51:55,390
Thinking about it, the greatest power of all powers is competence.

794
00:51:55,390 --> 00:51:56,490
Not violence.

795
00:51:56,490 --> 00:51:59,550
Ji Han, thank you, but you don't have to talk business here.

796
00:51:59,550 --> 00:52:01,960
It's fine. I did hear that.

797
00:52:01,960 --> 00:52:05,980
I didn't know you'd keep your promise with me this quickly.

798
00:52:05,980 --> 00:52:07,830
Thank you.

799
00:52:07,830 --> 00:52:10,920
Promise? You made a promise to Grandfather?

800
00:52:10,920 --> 00:52:12,960
What is it?

801
00:52:12,960 --> 00:52:18,020
All right, it's my turn to give you what I promised.

802
00:52:18,020 --> 00:52:20,830
That's why I asked you to come with me today.

803
00:52:23,870 --> 00:52:27,660
She must've asked for something big if the Myeongju City project was at stake.

804
00:52:27,660 --> 00:52:32,240
CEO Yoon, whatever that was, you'll be able to have it in no time.

805
00:52:32,240 --> 00:52:35,930
Because my grandfather always keeps his promises.

806
00:52:40,500 --> 00:52:42,580
Grandfather,

807
00:52:42,580 --> 00:52:44,900
would you like to watch a video?

808
00:52:44,900 --> 00:52:47,280
- A video? 
 - Yes.

809
00:52:47,280 --> 00:52:53,040
I actually recorded you and Do Han walking over here from behind you earlier without even knowing.

810
00:52:53,040 --> 00:52:55,020
Oh, really?

811
00:52:57,900 --> 00:53:03,830
I just have a habit of recording moments I don't want to forget.

812
00:53:05,480 --> 00:53:06,640
It's nice.

813
00:53:06,640 --> 00:53:08,450
This is the last picture.

814
00:53:08,450 --> 00:53:13,930
You can swipe left and look at them in reverse order.

815
00:53:16,070 --> 00:53:18,390
- Send me a copy of this one. 
- Yes.

816
00:53:18,390 --> 00:53:20,910
You had a talent like this, huh?

817
00:53:20,910 --> 00:53:22,600
Chairman.

818
00:53:24,150 --> 00:53:25,480
I have the car ready.

819
00:53:25,480 --> 00:53:28,110
Okay, let's go.

820
00:53:28,110 --> 00:53:30,800
Can you show me again next time you record something interesting?

821
00:53:30,800 --> 00:53:36,010
Of course, I have more interesting stuff on my phone besides this video.

822
00:53:37,070 --> 00:53:38,640
Let's go.

823
00:53:47,350 --> 00:53:49,220
I told you it's over if you show that video to others, right?

824
00:53:49,220 --> 00:53:53,060
Shut your mouth, or I might send it out to everyone now.

825
00:53:55,320 --> 00:53:57,360
Ji Han.

826
00:53:57,360 --> 00:54:02,480
You should come with me in my car with Chae Won.

827
00:54:02,480 --> 00:54:05,110
- Me? 
 - Why? You don't want to?

828
00:54:05,110 --> 00:54:07,000
No, that's not the case, but—

829
00:54:07,000 --> 00:54:09,480
I thought about this and

830
00:54:09,480 --> 00:54:13,700
I realized I never got to spend time alone with Ji Han.

831
00:54:13,700 --> 00:54:18,220
Let's go back together and have dinner, and I have something to tell you, too.

832
00:54:18,220 --> 00:54:19,840
You're okay with it, right, Chae Won?

833
00:54:19,840 --> 00:54:22,060
- Yes. 
 - And you? You don't want to?

834
00:54:22,060 --> 00:54:23,910
I'd love to have dinner.

835
00:54:23,910 --> 00:54:26,680
That settles it, then. Let's go.

836
00:54:31,320 --> 00:54:36,670
As I expected, this is your car, right, Chairman?

837
00:54:36,670 --> 00:54:39,070
You came to remember her with your grandchildren.

838
00:54:39,070 --> 00:54:41,720
How nice you all look.

839
00:54:41,720 --> 00:54:43,880
CEO Yoon Chae Won is here, too, huh?

840
00:54:43,880 --> 00:54:46,000
Did you like the picture I took last time?

841
00:54:46,000 --> 00:54:48,040
That's enough.

842
00:54:48,040 --> 00:54:49,930
What business do you have here?

843
00:54:49,930 --> 00:54:51,380
While I was at it, you know.

844
00:54:51,380 --> 00:54:54,220
It's Hyeon Soo Hyeon's memorial day, so I'll wish her peace.

845
00:54:54,220 --> 00:54:57,910
And find material for my articles if I happen to run into you.

846
00:54:57,910 --> 00:55:00,620
Everyone's dying to write about your third grandson,

847
00:55:00,620 --> 00:55:03,560
but we know nothing, and it's driving us nuts.

848
00:55:04,700 --> 00:55:07,360
Oh, yes, t-this right here.

849
00:55:08,310 --> 00:55:09,770
Is it because of my age?

850
00:55:09,770 --> 00:55:15,360
It aches here every time it rains, so I can't even investigate like I used to.

851
00:55:15,360 --> 00:55:18,510
Oh, that's right. Isn't it the same for you?

852
00:55:18,510 --> 00:55:20,350
After you got injured back then.

853
00:55:20,350 --> 00:55:24,100
How dare you show up here and act out?

854
00:55:24,100 --> 00:55:26,850
- How dare you show up here! 
 - Sir.

855
00:55:26,850 --> 00:55:28,810
- You— 
 - G-Grandfather—

856
00:55:28,810 --> 00:55:30,270
Let go, you brat!

857
00:55:30,270 --> 00:55:32,910
It's not like I can't come here when I'm also a victim of the incident.

858
00:55:32,910 --> 00:55:34,680
So you should answer your phone!

859
00:55:34,680 --> 00:55:38,620
I can't help but come to where you are if you keep avoiding me!

860
00:55:42,410 --> 00:55:44,820
By the way, who is she?

861
00:55:44,820 --> 00:55:47,880
Ji Han, take care of A Jeong for me.

862
00:56:10,520 --> 00:56:14,540
I'm fine, so stop looking and focus on driving.

863
00:56:15,600 --> 00:56:17,250
You're not okay, huh?

864
00:56:17,250 --> 00:56:20,720
People who aren't okay always say they are.

865
00:56:58,360 --> 00:57:00,520
What are you doing? Slow down.

866
00:57:00,520 --> 00:57:02,610
Don't you see the car tailing us?

867
00:57:02,610 --> 00:57:05,060
We'll get caught if I slow down.

868
00:57:05,060 --> 00:57:07,950
But this isn't the right way. Where are you going right now?

869
00:57:07,950 --> 00:57:09,790
I'm the driver. I'll figure it out.

870
00:57:09,790 --> 00:57:14,330
- You just hold tight on the handle. 
  - Recalculating the route. 

871
00:57:24,260 --> 00:57:25,980
Na A Jeong!

872
00:57:32,040 --> 00:57:34,890
Na A Jeong, stop!

873
00:57:47,030 --> 00:57:49,460
Stop, please!

874
00:57:54,730 --> 00:57:58,610
Oh, yes. This is Reporter Kang Ik Joon. Yes.

875
00:57:58,610 --> 00:58:02,600
The offer you made last time. I'll accept it.

876
00:58:02,600 --> 00:58:06,620
I was only going to test it out, but it's more interesting than I thought.

877
00:58:07,570 --> 00:58:12,370
Those brothers and the lady named Na A Jeong.

878
00:58:23,150 --> 00:58:25,340
Gosh, what?

879
00:58:26,190 --> 00:58:30,020
We were able to lose that reporter, thanks to me.

880
00:58:30,020 --> 00:58:34,250
Otherwise, my guess is we would've gone for round two.

881
00:58:34,250 --> 00:58:37,030
I would've had round two with you.

882
00:58:37,030 --> 00:58:40,420
Do you know how many times I banged my head?

883
00:58:56,150 --> 00:58:57,830
It's fine now, right?

884
00:58:57,830 --> 00:58:59,200
What was that just now?

885
00:58:59,200 --> 00:59:02,500
What do you think? I was pampering you.

886
00:59:02,500 --> 00:59:04,480
So why?

887
00:59:04,480 --> 00:59:08,560
Any other day, you would've beat me up to a pulp with that mouth of yours.

888
00:59:11,460 --> 00:59:14,350
Lee Ji Han, you were hurt earlier.

889
00:59:15,140 --> 00:59:19,430
Because Grandfather did this.

890
00:59:20,150 --> 00:59:25,640
I don't want to get mad at you to add to that and trample on your feelings.

891
00:59:28,270 --> 00:59:32,460
I don't wish to console you about something I don't even know about.

892
00:59:32,460 --> 00:59:35,940
I don't want to be nosy and get involved thoughtlessly, either.

893
00:59:36,910 --> 00:59:40,400
But I think I can hear you out like this.

894
00:59:41,300 --> 00:59:46,150
Your complaints and whining, Lee Ji Han. Stuff like that.

895
00:59:48,600 --> 00:59:50,920
So you can tell me everything.

896
00:59:50,920 --> 00:59:54,310
I'll hear you out and forget it all.

897
00:59:54,310 --> 00:59:57,800
Did I ever tell you I'm good at things like that?

898
01:00:10,100 --> 01:00:12,600
Is your stomach feeling all right?

899
01:00:14,320 --> 01:00:17,460
Should I ask for another cup of water or something?

900
01:00:19,120 --> 01:00:21,230
I don't need water.

901
01:00:22,500 --> 01:00:25,360
Let's go outside for some air.

902
01:00:54,670 --> 01:00:57,390
Why did you come to the department store that day?

903
01:00:58,700 --> 01:01:02,580
I'm sure you didn't come by to eavesdrop on me badmouthing you.

904
01:01:02,580 --> 01:01:04,670
How surprising.

905
01:01:04,670 --> 01:01:08,620
You know that, yet you still haven't apologized.

906
01:01:09,900 --> 01:01:13,460
I went there to try to get on your good side.

907
01:01:15,170 --> 01:01:17,120
Someone told me this.

908
01:01:17,120 --> 01:01:20,000
Since you think dearly of your brother,

909
01:01:20,000 --> 01:01:24,330
you'd be optimistic about this marriage once I get on your good side.

910
01:01:25,960 --> 01:01:29,900
You seem to enjoy looking up at trees you can't even climb, Na A Jeong.

911
01:01:30,700 --> 01:01:34,870
I said this before, but I really think you're shrewd.

912
01:01:36,280 --> 01:01:38,930
I'm sorry for not telling you

913
01:01:38,930 --> 01:01:41,790
about New York and the marriage papers.

914
01:01:43,750 --> 01:01:50,230
As you said, I might not be the perfect partner for Do Han.

915
01:01:50,230 --> 01:01:56,060
But he wouldn't be suffering while living a life he doesn't want if he's with me, right?

916
01:01:56,060 --> 01:02:01,040
If it's a marriage I must go through in the end, I only want blessings.

917
01:02:01,040 --> 01:02:04,330
I don't even wish to get on your good side.

918
01:02:04,330 --> 01:02:06,950
Can't you just watch us?

919
01:02:07,620 --> 01:02:10,500
I'll be really good to Do Han.

920
01:02:16,450 --> 01:02:18,050
How is he doing?

921
01:02:18,050 --> 01:02:20,360
He fell asleep just now.

922
01:02:20,360 --> 01:02:23,580
Don't come out. I'll go on my own.

923
01:02:23,580 --> 01:02:25,870
It's related to Ji Han, right?

924
01:02:25,870 --> 01:02:28,520
The promise you and Grandfather made.

925
01:02:33,370 --> 01:02:36,630
Hey, let me ask you the question I asked you before again.

926
01:02:36,630 --> 01:02:39,980
Yoon Chae Won, do you like Ji Han?

927
01:02:40,780 --> 01:02:44,650
What Grandfather promised to give you. Is it Lee Ji Han?

928
01:02:45,550 --> 01:02:47,400
You really—

929
01:02:47,400 --> 01:02:49,740
Did you make a deal with my grandfather over my brother?

930
01:02:49,740 --> 01:02:51,460
Yes, I did.

931
01:02:51,460 --> 01:02:53,620
Why? Am I not allowed to?

932
01:02:53,620 --> 01:02:55,380
Of course not!

933
01:02:55,380 --> 01:02:57,300
Ji Han doesn't know about it.

934
01:02:57,300 --> 01:03:00,060
You should decide that after asking him, at least.

935
01:03:00,060 --> 01:03:05,290
Do Han, you know you're being absurd as you say that. Right?

936
01:03:05,290 --> 01:03:10,330
Deciding things without asking Ji Han's opinion is what you do best.

937
01:03:11,500 --> 01:03:14,630
Don't worry. I'll take my time and tell him.

938
01:03:14,630 --> 01:03:17,660
Because I don't want Ji Han to get hurt, either.

939
01:03:17,660 --> 01:03:19,080
He's precious to me, too.

940
01:03:19,080 --> 01:03:20,400
What if Ji Han says no?

941
01:03:20,400 --> 01:03:22,300
You said I was Ji Han's first love.

942
01:03:22,300 --> 01:03:26,910
You also know Ji Han's ideal type has been me since he was a kid.

943
01:03:26,910 --> 01:03:33,700
Such feelings wouldn't suddenly disappear or turn for someone else, would they?

944
01:03:33,700 --> 01:03:35,540
I'm leaving.

945
01:03:59,420 --> 01:04:01,740
Where are we going right now?

946
01:04:17,000 --> 01:04:21,170
   

947
01:04:23,680 --> 01:04:26,500
I'm sorry for lying.

948
01:04:27,520 --> 01:04:30,600
Though I'm a fake daughter-in-law,

949
01:04:30,600 --> 01:04:34,130
I'll take good care of your son.

950
01:04:35,610 --> 01:04:38,790
So please don't be too worried there.

951
01:05:33,110 --> 01:05:35,570
You've gone mad, Lee Ji Han.

952
01:05:36,270 --> 01:05:38,390
You've finally gone mad.

